Solution Overview: 


Technical Details
Code link: https://gemini.google.com/share/35d816f6722e.  
Git repository:
str-zz/finalstr-zz.: Final Project repository 

The technical components of the web app that is being presented and developed can be split into two sections: Formulaic estimation and a simple neural network model. The formulaic estimation web application was built on a successful gemini.ai generated code, which used three different languages. However, this was not enough to create a model nor did it include any aspect of artificial intelligence (AI) and its subfields. In order to tie the original estimation and machine learning, a subfield of Artificial Intelligence, TensorFlow.js was added to the original code to create an extremely simple, basic version of a neural network, commonly known as a linear regression model. 

The formulaic estimation section of the web application uses mathematical concepts– it is fixed and uses the four core operations: multiplication, division, addition, and subtraction. These calculations create the estimated Total Daily Dose (TDD) that appears when the application is used. On its own, this is not a model nor does it include any branches of artificial intelligence. 

To create a model, TensorFlow.js added, which allows for gemini.ai to integrate a machine learning model within the code without needing nor creating an actual model. With TensorFlow.js	integrated, the code is capable of predicting a “refinement” factor, an attribute found within machine learning models. This was a necessary step because access to patient records is not available, which causes restrictions on the creation of a dataset for the model to be built. 


Core calculations
Total daily dose (mg) = weight (kg) * dosing factor (mg/kg/day)
Dose per administration = Total daily dose / frequency
Body surface area = square root [(weight in kg * height in cm)/3600]
Adjustment factor =  (-5 * Norm Weight) + (10 * Norm Age) + 10
ML adjusted TDD midpoint = Standard TDD + (Adjustment factor * 10)
Dose per administration = ML adjusted TDD midpoint / dosing frequency 
Total deviation = (Weight dev * 0.4) + (Age Dev * 0.3) + (Factor dev * 0.3)
Error margin = 0.05 + (0.20 - 0.05) * Total dev
Confidence score = (1- error margin) * 100










